The paper deals with a transport layer protocol for network communication, which suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also discusses algorithms for packet scheduling, which could fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper addresses the issue of packet delivery and reliability, which could be relevant to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm to optimize network resource utilization, which could be related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
